Phase 9: TypeScript Completion + Code Modernization
====================================================

## Summary

Converted all source files from JavaScript to TypeScript with strict mode,
migrated test runner from react-scripts/Jest to Vitest, updated ESLint to
flat config with typescript-eslint, added React.StrictMode, and cleaned up
Vite config by removing JS-as-JSX workarounds.

## Commits (8 steps)

1. `feat: add TypeScript + Vitest deps, remove react-scripts (Phase 9, Step 1)`
2. `feat: rename source files to .ts/.tsx, create types.ts (Phase 9, Step 2)`
3. `feat: add TypeScript annotations, enable strict mode (Phase 9, Steps 3-4)`
4. `feat: migrate Jest to Vitest (Phase 9, Step 5)`
5. `feat: update ESLint to flat config (Phase 9, Step 6)`
6. `feat: wrap app in React.StrictMode (Phase 9, Step 7)`
7. `feat: clean up Vite config, add vitest/globals types (Phase 9, Step 8)`

## Packages

### Added (devDependencies)
- `vitest` — test runner (replaces react-scripts test)
- `@vitest/coverage-v8` — coverage provider
- `jsdom` — browser environment for vitest
- `@typescript-eslint/parser` — TypeScript parser for ESLint
- `@typescript-eslint/eslint-plugin` — TypeScript ESLint rules
- `@eslint/js` — ESLint recommended config for flat config
- `typescript-eslint` — flat config helper
- `globals` — browser/node/serviceworker globals for ESLint
- `@types/react` — React type definitions
- `@types/react-dom` — ReactDOM type definitions
- `@types/uuid` — uuid type definitions

### Upgraded
- `@testing-library/jest-dom` ^4.2.4 → ^6.9.1 (Vitest compatibility)

### Removed
- `react-scripts` ^2.1.3 — no longer needed (Vite handles dev/build, Vitest handles tests)
- `babel-eslint` (referenced in .eslintrc, transitive dep from react-scripts)
- `.env` (contained only `SKIP_PREFLIGHT_CHECK=true` for react-scripts)
- `src/react-app-env.d.ts` (react-scripts reference types)
- `cheerio` override in package.json (was only for react-scripts Jest)

### Moved
- `eslint-plugin-react` from dependencies → devDependencies

